profile_positions.description:
- Initiating and further developing research-based advocacy towards governments and international actors; 
- Maintaining a network of interested experts, academics, civil society groups and policymakers to advance PAX's agenda on enviromental consequences of conflicts and armed drones proliferation; 
- Contributing to (field) research and analysis around the environmental and climate dimensions of armed conflict, and drone proliferation.

- Research, analysis and reporting about political, security and humanitarian developments in Ukraine, with a focus on domestic politics and reform agenda, security developments, and human rights; 
- Delivering daily media briefs to Ambassador and Political Section;
- Drafting statements, speeches, press materials and talking points on the topics of Sweden's interests in Ukraine;
- Preparing state visits of Swedish officials to Ukraine, including those of Prime Minister and Foreign Minister; 
- Preparing and organizing meetings and events for Ambassador and Political Section in Kyiv and in other regions of Ukraine; 
- Maintaining and expanding a network in political circles, civil society, media and the international community.

Monitoring political developments in Ukraine and reporting to the DPPA at UN HQ, which implied: 
- preparation of daily/weekly updates on political and conflict-related developments; 
- writing analytical papers and drafting reports; 
- organizing and attending meetings with relevant Ukrainian and international stakeholders.

Preparation of the Ukraine Reform Conference in Copenhagen as part of Danish organizing team:
- provided political inputs (agendas, progress reports, background briefings, statements, speeches, etc.) to a successful international conference that gathered 14 foreign ministers and other senior officials from Europe and North America;
- advised the Embassy and the MFA on political and reform processes in Ukraine;
- conducted international advocacy around Ukraine's reforms in Copenhagen, Kyiv and Brussels through reform-related events;
- developed communication strategy around the conference and Denmark's reform support in Ukraine.

Participation in the Canada-Ukraine Parliamentary Program as an intern in the office of Canada's Shadow Minister for National Defence, which implied the following responsibilities: 
- defence and security policy research for the National Defence Committee;
- drafting various communication products (speeches, social media publications,
correspondence with constituents);
- providing briefings on Ukraine-related topics to Canadian MPs;
- organization of public diplomacy activities promoting Ukraine in Canada.

The Institute for Euro-Atlantic Cooperation (IEAC) is an independent Ukrainian think-tank performing research and advocacy projects which promote democracy, rule of law, support security sector reforms and strengthen Ukrainian civil society. 
The primary topics of the IEAC interest cover international relations, foreign policy, defense and security.
As the IEAC project assistant, I was responsible for the following tasks:
- developing project proposals and preparing grant applications;
- organization of events (round-tables, debates, press-conferences);
- writing agendas, briefing notes, analytical reports;
- communication and administrative management.
